{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 24, "timestamp": 1771865784, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "Sift: Claude Code Integration"}
[0.003654, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[2J\u001b[3J"]
[0.003899, "o", "=== Connecting Sift to Claude Code ===\r\n\r\n"]
[2.005427, "o", "Step 1: Build the Sift binary\r\n\r\ng"]
[2.037104, "o", "o"]
[2.068612, "o", " "]
[2.100371, "o", "b"]
[2.132311, "o", "u"]
[2.164205, "o", "i"]
[2.196031, "o", "l"]
[2.228111, "o", "d"]
[2.260024, "o", " "]
[2.291559, "o", "-"]
[2.323312, "o", "o"]
[2.354514, "o", " "]
[2.385927, "o", "s"]
[2.417334, "o", "i"]
[2.4491, "o", "f"]
[2.480682, "o", "t"]
[2.512336, "o", " "]
[2.544072, "o", "."]
[2.575309, "o", "/"]
[2.606698, "o", "c"]
[2.63829, "o", "m"]
[2.669954, "o", "d"]
[2.701391, "o", "/"]
[2.732792, "o", "s"]
[2.764075, "o", "e"]
[2.795262, "o", "r"]
[2.827084, "o", "v"]
[2.858705, "o", "e"]
[2.889944, "o", "r"]
[2.921473, "o", "\r\n"]
[3.923201, "o", "  Done. Single binary, no dependencies.\r\n\r\n"]
[5.924838, "o", "Step 2: Add MCP configuration\r\n\r\n  Add this to .mcp.json in your project root:\r\n\r\n  {\r\n    \"mcpServers\": {\r\n      \"sift\": {\r\n        \"type\": \"stdio\",\r\n        \"command\": \"/absolute/path/to/sift\",\r\n        \"env\": {\r\n          \"SIFT_DB_PATH\": \"/absolute/path/to/sift.db\"\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n"]
[8.926959, "o", "Step 3: Restart Claude Code - tools appear automatically\r\n\r\n  Claude Code now has 6 new tools:\r\n    - mcp__sift__ingest_report\r\n    - mcp__sift__analyze_results\r\n    - mcp__sift__get_report_stats\r\n    - mcp__sift__get_failure_history\r\n    - mcp__sift__get_flaky_tests\r\n    - mcp__sift__get_severity_trend\r\n\r\n"]
[11.928711, "o", "Step 4: Use it naturally\r\n\r\n  You say: \"Run my tests and analyze the failures with Sift\"\r\n\r\n"]
[13.930518, "o", "  Claude Code will:\r\n    1. Run your test suite (pytest, go test, mvn test, etc.)\r\n    2. Encode the JUnit XML report\r\n    3. Call mcp__sift__ingest_report\r\n    4. Read the structured analysis\r\n    5. Give you actionable suggestions based on root causes\r\n\r\n"]
[16.93245, "o", "--- Example: What Claude Code sees after ingestion ---\r\n\r\n"]
[17.997298, "o", "  Summary: 220/308 tests failed from 3 root causes (12 original, 84 cascading). Categories: 94 infrastructure, 2 assertion. 96 new since last run.\r\n\r\n  Group 1: Docker daemon not available (required by Testcontainers)\r\n           [infrastructure] 56 tests (6 original, 50 cascade)\r\n  Group 2: DataSource not configured: org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanCreationException: Error creating bean with name 'dataSource': Failed to configure a DataSource: 'url'\r\n           [infrastructure] 38 tests (4 original, 34 cascade)\r\n  Group 3: Expected status 404 but was 400\r\n           [assertion] 2 tests (2 original, 0 cascade)\r\n\r\n"]
[17.997339, "o", "  Cascade detection: 88% of failures were cascading noise\r\n  Only 12 root failures to investigate (not 220)\r\n"]
[21.003081, "o", "\r\n--- What Claude Code tells you ---\r\n\r\n"]
